 throne, which were resolved by the victory of William the Conqueror at the Battle of Hastings. His memory was honoured by Normans and English alike, for his fairness and his piety. Edward's mother was Norman; he had spent part of his youth in Normandy; and William claimed to have been nominated by Edward as his successor. Edward was canonized in the 12th century, and came to be venerated throughout Europe as a model of a Christian king."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Oswulf de Haverington of Flemingby was born about 1151, in Harrington, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom as the son of Gunnilda Dunbar. He had at least 1 son with Christina de Workington. He died in 1190, in Cumberland, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 40."},"et":{"Abt 1151–1190":"umbes 1151–1190","1151–1190":"1151–1190","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1189–1235":"1189–1235","1081–Female":"1081–Surnud","1190":"1190","Abt 1151":"umbes 1151","1235":"1235","Abt 1189":"umbes 1189","1189":"1189","1155":"1155","1151":"1151","Abt 1160":"umbes 1160","1081":"1081","Harrington, Cumberland, England":"Harrington, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Haverington, Cumberland, England":"Harrington, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1151–1190":"noin 1151–1190","1151–1190":"1151–1190","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1189–1235":"1189–1235","1081–Female":"1081–Kuollut","1190":"1190","Abt 1151":"noin 1151","1235":"1235","Abt 1189":"noin 1189","1189":"1189","1155":"1155","1151":"1151","Abt 1160":"noin 1160","1081":"1081","Harrington, Cumberland, England":"Harrington, Cumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Haverington, Cumberland, England":"Harrington, Cumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Cumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1151–1190":"environ 1151–1190","1151–1190":"1151–1190","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1189–1235":"1189–1235","1081–Female":"1081–Dé